<div class="sub-content-header">Still the World's Largest Consumer Technology Tradeshow!</div>
<br />

<IMG height=179 hspace=10 src="/images/photos/Arch2.jpg" width=250 align=right vspace=10>An independent audit, performed by VERIS Consulting LLC, verified all attendance numbers and confirmed the International CES as the world's largest consumer technology tradeshow and America's largest annual tradeshow of any kind. Two thousand seven hundred exhibitors showcased their latest products on more than 1.7 million net square feet of exhibit space, with a total of 113,085 in attendance. 
<P>CES attracts the "who's who" of the technology and related industries, including C-level executives from the entertainment, wireless and consumer electronics industries. More than 4,500 attendees represented companies with more than $500 million in total annual sales.</P>
<P><A href="/docs/2009AuditSummary.pdf" target=_blank>Download your copy of the 2009 Audit Summary now</A>!</P>
<P><STRONG>2009 International CES Attendees</STRONG> <BR>•&nbsp;Exhibits-only Attendees: 65,726 <BR>•&nbsp;Exhibitors: 38,318 <BR>•&nbsp;Conference Attendees: 1,997 <BR>•&nbsp;Press: 4,563 <BR>•&nbsp;Blogger: 471<BR>•&nbsp;Financial and Market Analysts: 1,513 <BR>•&nbsp;Speakers: 497<BR>•&nbsp;Total: 113,085</P>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3027"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Last Chance to Reserve Space at SINOCES</div>
<br />

<IMG height=60 hspace=10 src="/images/content/SINOCES_LOGO_180.jpg" width=180 align=right vspace=10>
<P>Two of China’s largest CE manufacturers, <STRONG>Haier</STRONG> and <STRONG>Hisense</STRONG>, will have a large presence at <A href="http://www.sinoces.com/cn/index.htm" target=_blank>SINOCES </A>July 9-12, 2009, in Qingdao, China. International CE manufacturers <STRONG>HP</STRONG>, <STRONG>Panasonic</STRONG>, <STRONG>Dolby</STRONG>, <STRONG>Canon</STRONG> and <STRONG>Lenovo</STRONG> will also display their latest product offerings alongside 450 other exhibitors across more than 37,500 net square meters of exhibit space. SINOCES will attract an estimated 70,000 CE industry professionals from around the globe. <A href="http://www.sinoces.com/en/exhibitor_all.aspx" target=_blank>Will they see you there</A>?</P>
<P>Learn about exhibiting at SINOCES. <A href="mailto:%20bmoon@ce.org" target=_blank>Contact a business development representative</A>.</P>
<P>The show is certified by the U.S. Department of Commerce export trade promotion program. As part of this certification, the Department of Commerce is sponsoring a pavilion for U.S. manufacturers and service providers. <A href="mailto:%20jtkelley@ce.org" target=_blank>Contact us for details regarding the U.S. pavilion</A>.</P>
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3026"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Rise to the Challenge at i-stage in Phoenix</div>
<br />

<IMG height=99 hspace=10 src="/images/content/istage175.jpg" width=175 align=right vspace=5><A href="http://i-stage.ce.org/" target=_blank>i-stage</A> is the proving ground for next-gen technologies – a chance for developing products, services and applications to show off their selling points and duke it out for the title of most promising powerhouse. The competition is free to enter and is a direct route to <A href="http://i-stage.ce.org/" target=_blank>more than $50,000 in prizes</A> and a dynamic debut at the International CES, the annual big bang of innovation.&nbsp; Entries for the 2009 i-stage competition are now being <A href="http://i-stage.ce.org/?page_id=4" target=_blank>accepted through July 31, 2009</A>. The live competition will take place during CEA Industry Forum on October 19 in Phoenix, AZ.
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3025"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Sponsor the Innovations 2010 Awards!</div>
<br />

<IMG height=150 hspace=10 src="/images/content/CES_251_2k10_Innovations.jpg" width=98 align=right vspace=5><A href="http://www.cesweb.org/awards/innovations/default.asp" target=_blank>The International CES® Innovations 2010 Design and Engineering Awards</A>&nbsp; is the most impressive and renowned awards program in the consumer technology industry. Thousands of industry leaders and press will flock to the Innovations 2010 Design and Engineering Awards Showcase at the 2010 CES to witness the “next big thing”.<BR><BR>The Innovations 2010 call for sponsors is now open. Gain incredible exposure in the months leading up to CES and see your company featured among the most creative in the industry at the Innovations Showcase. Choose to be either a premier sponsor of the entire program, or sponsor the on-site awards stage. Either way, the coverage you’ll receive is unbeatable. <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/sponsorships/contactRep.asp" target=_blank>Contact a CES sponsorship representative</A>&nbsp; today!
        <br /><img width="1" height="20" src="/images/framework/spacer.gif"/>
        <img height="15" alt="" src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif"/><br />

<a name="3024"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Reserve Your Product-Specific Exhibit Space Today</div>
<br />

<IMG height=45 hspace=10 src="/images/content/techzone.jpg" width=200 align=right vspace=10>If you're from a small new company or represent an emerging technology, consider participation in one of our <A href="/exhibits/displays/techZones.asp" target=_blank>2010 International CES TechZones</A>. Here, attendees learn more about up-and-coming players in various technologies such as e-books, netbooks, social media platforms as well as related web-based and mobile applications. Jump-start your CES exhibit experience in one of these and other market-specific areas.
<P>For more information, please contact 703-907-7645 or <A href="mailto:exhibit@CE.org">exhibit@CE.org</A>.<BR></P>
